# AI Job Hunter — Project Rules

Local-first Electron desktop app. pnpm monorepo. React 19 + TypeScript strict.
ESLint `--max-warnings 0` in CI — every warning is a build failure.

---

## Shell

**Always use Bash (never PowerShell). Prefix every command with `rtk`:**
`rtk pnpm build` · `rtk git status` · `rtk rg foo` · `rtk fd src`
Meta commands: `rtk gain` (savings stats) · `rtk discover` (missed opportunities).

---

## Non-negotiable — never bypass these rules

ESLint enforces all of the below in CI. Inline suppression is banned (`noInlineConfig: true`).

### Zero errors before marking complete

- `rtk pnpm lint:strict` — zero ESLint errors/warnings
- `rtk pnpm typecheck` — zero TypeScript errors
- No `console.log` in production code
- No `@ts-ignore`, `@ts-expect-error`, or `// eslint-disable`

### Branch + PR workflow

Never push to `main`. `rtk git checkout -b feat/name` → commit → `rtk git push -u origin <branch>` → `rtk gh pr create` → CI passes → user approves.

Verify branch before starting:
```bash
rtk git fetch origin && rtk git branch -r | grep $(git branch --show-current)
# If gone: rtk git checkout main && rtk git pull origin main
```

---

## Architecture

```
packages/shared    → IPC contracts, types, Zod schemas. No React, no Node.
packages/ui        → React component library (@ajh/ui). No app logic.
packages/prompts   → AI prompt templates. Pure TS, zero deps.
packages/core/ai/data/workers → Main process only. Never import in renderer.
apps/desktop/src/renderer     → React UI. No Node.js access.
```

Renderer → main: `window.api.*` only (via `AppClient` context → service hooks).

---

## Rules (ESLint-enforced, violations fail CI)

**1. Service hooks only** — never call `window.api.*` in components/routes. Use `@/services`.

**2. i18n adapter** — `import { useTranslation } from '@/lib/i18n'`, not `react-i18next`.

**3. No hardcoded colors** — use `text-brand`, `text-brand-soft`, `bg-brand`, `border-brand`. No `[#RRGGBB]`.

**4. Motion tokens** — `import { transition } from '@/lib/motion'` → `transition.normal` etc. No inline objects.

**5. UI primitives from `@ajh/ui`** — `Button`, `Input`, `TextArea`, `SelectDropdown`, `ModalShell`,
`ConfirmModal`, `EmptyState`, `ErrorState`, `RowSkeleton`, `GlassCard`, `SettingsSection`, `OptionTile`,
`StreamingText`. `PageShell` from `@/components/layout/PageShell`. No raw `<button>`, `<select>`, `<textarea>`.

**6. Package imports** — `@ajh/ui` directly, not `@/components/ui/*`. Prefer `React.ComponentProps<typeof X>`.

**7. Import order** (auto-fixed by `rtk pnpm lint:fix`) — `node:*` → external → `@ajh/*` → `@/*` → relative.

**8. Type imports** — `import type` for pure types. ESLint auto-fixes.

**9. Data fetching** — React Query via service hooks only. No `useState + useEffect` for remote data.

**10. Package boundaries** — renderer never imports `@ajh/core`, `@ajh/ai`, `@ajh/data`, `@ajh/workers`.

**11. New IPC capability** — contract → router → preload → service hook → query key (all 5 steps required).

